role_summary: We are seeking a Frontend Engineer to join our software engineering team. You will play a key role in developing and optimizing frontend applications, ensuring seamless integration with backend systems, and delivering high-quality user experiences. This role offers opportunities to take on increasing responsibility based on experience, contributing to both technical execution and team-wide improvements.
responsibilities: Develop and maintain scalable, high-performance frontend solutions.
Write clean, maintainable, and well-documented code following industry best practices.
Collaborate closely with backend engineers, UI/UX designers, and product managers to build cohesive and user-friendly applications.
Participate in and contribute to code reviews, ensuring code quality, maintainability, and adherence to team standards.
Optimize frontend performance to ensure fast, responsive user experiences across browsers and devices.
Implement modern UI/UX best practices to enhance usability and accessibility.
Contribute to the evolution of frontend architecture, tooling, and development processes.
Troubleshoot and debug frontend issues, proactively addressing technical debt and improving system reliability.
Stay up to date with emerging frontend technologies and advocate for relevant improvements.

required: Experience in frontend software engineering, with a track record of delivering production-ready applications.
Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field, or equivalent work experience.
Proficiency in HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and React.
Understanding of frontend build tools, package managers, and CI/CD pipelines.
Strong problem-solving skills and the ability to debug complex frontend issues.
Effective communication skills, with the ability to collaborate across engineering, product, and design teams.
Passion for building intuitive, high-quality user interfaces and continuously improving frontend performance.
nice_to_have: Experience working with TypeScript.
Knowledge of frontend testing frameworks, especially Playwright.
Familiarity with REST or other API interaction patterns.
Exposure to design systems and component-based architecture.

compensation.notes: The actual offer, reflecting the total compensation package and benefits, will be determined by a number of factors including the applicant's experience, knowledge, skills, and abilities, as well as internal equity among our team.
